OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1782776882
OL,3,CShop price inflation remains unchanged
OL,4,Cdespite warnings of Middle East knock-
OL,5,Con
OL,7,FShop price inflation remained
OL,8,Funchanged in June despite warnings of
OL,9,Flooming price hikes as a result of the
OL,10,FMiddle East crisis.
OL,12,FPrices remained 1.2% higher than a
OL,13,Fyear ago in June, although this was
OL,14,Fabove the three-month average of 1.1%,
OL,15,Fthe British Retail Consortium (BRC)
OL,16,Fand NIQ said.
OL,18,FInflation on non-food products
OL,19,Fincreased slightly to 0.6% from May's
OL,20,F0.5%, but food inflation fell to 2.4%
OL,21,Ffrom 2.7%.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/6
