OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1782776882
OL,3,CShop price inflation remains unchanged
OL,4,Cdespite warnings of Middle East knock-
OL,5,Con
OL,7,FFresh food inflation saw a significant
OL,8,Ffall to 2.8% from May's 3.4%, as
OL,9,Fbumper crops of local produce helped
OL,10,Fto keep prices down.
OL,12,FBRC chief executive Helen Dickinson
OL,13,Fsaid: "Food price growth eased, and as
OL,14,Fshoppers made the most of the
OL,15,Fsunshine, retailers helped keep the
OL,16,Fprices of summer treats such as
OL,17,Fstrawberries and ice cream low thanks
OL,18,Fto bumper crops and strong competition.
OL,26,@uD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
